summary:
I learned at a very early age that I was an empathetic person who enjoyed helping people find solutions to their problems. My personal journey has taken many turns, but there were always some common elements: being a bridge for communication between people and helping others to meet their needs. 
I was raised with influences from different cultures and having lived in other countries, made me realise how vast the world is and how diverse the people in it are.
My background in the performing arts allows me to be in touch with the feelings of the people around me, which I consider to be a great advantage when developing products that add value to people's lives. 
My experience in adult language teaching gave me the ability to discover the different paths that each individual takes to reach a goal and how they can all be valid.
I have a quick and curious mind, and if a subject interests me, I will always want to investigate a little more. I am a person who is detail oriented but doesn't lose sight of the big picture. I am a team player and also know how to work independently. I'm eager to keep discovering the amazing world of user experience design!
